name: Silver Diner
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Hilda Kroll', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100441671474418921617/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu3KGRjm1HlFubHchXb-qe4Am5wpKuzTMu0W_djM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '5 months ago', 'text': 'Great place for comfort food, especially on a cold, rainy day.  My friend got the combo salad and chili.  I got the Ribeye Philly Steak on a sweet potato sub roll.  The side of honey pepper relish was something different and really good.  Looks like a real, old fashioned diner like the one I knew as a teenager.  Now, I appreciate the ten percent discount for seniors.', 'time': 1650313582, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Cecilia Sterling', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109844148801004404726/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu0ZE22R6pUcsNqFp88R3kmfFkr73xGyTG5PO_Ur=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': "I had the lemony hummus with cauliflower pita bread and it was delicious. The sweet potato fries are very good too. The serving sizes are smaller than at other restaurants. I definitely felt like I could eat some more after I finished my meal. Also it's a little pricey for the small serving size. The hummus pita dish was around $16 I think. For that amount of money I want a good filling meal that doesn't leave me still feeling hungry. But if you don't want large portion sizes this might be a good restaurant for you.

I went at lunch time on a Friday and it was very busy, the parking lot was very full and I had to park far from the restaurant. However there was no line or wait time so that was great. It did take awhile for our food to be prepared. Maybe 20 or 30 minutes. The staff were polite but seemed harried and overwhelmed due to the busyness. They did get our orders correct, so that was good. I wasn't sure with how distracted our waiter was what we'd end up getting. Overall a good experience. Family and children friendly. Competent, friendly service. Great kids menu. Comparatively good prices and great food! Love my Luau burger!
Also, their booths are partitioned nicely with the glass dividers that go up pretty high. Overall good experience üëç', 'time': 1661437646, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Natalie Neal', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109170761892909230679/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu1pwaZTBwcH8Z2b78GWqlZEuUA2iDNTbjO1IRXl=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '4 weeks ago', 'text': "I continue to be amazed by the quality of food and drinks at silver diner. I was at a bougie restaurant for brunch in Old Town, and their food and mimosas didn't come close to the quality of this silver diner. I got the tropical mimosa which is guava mint, and it was delicious! I also got the oat protein pancakes, with coconut almond whipped cream. It was a delicious pairing, I just wish the pancakes were cooked a little more in the middle. The staff was also very friendly, and there was no wait because I got to sit at the counter. Highly recommend this place for local brunch", 'time': 1662937865, 'translated': False}]

name: Bertucci's Italian Restaurant
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Petter Llanos', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107562420826062445748/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-F70H7r72qxOEh6iKmMVf8ya6IEf7TAx5KPZg6Ag=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': "Bertucci's restaurant is one of the most terrible experience that I had in a restaurant. Please, avoid a bad time and waste your money over there.
I arrived 8:15pm, and the place is closing at 9:30pm. My wife and I ordered simple food: Bertucci's platter as starter ( 4 chicken wings, 2 garlic bread, 2 meatball, 2 grilled cheese), 1 lasagna, and 1 chicken Parmigiano. The garlic bread was not fresh made today, the consistency indicated it was made a day ago as sooner. The lasagna supposed made in a brick oven came totally cold in the center. This issue happened when you change the brick oven by microwave. The waitress was so nice, and that disaster was not her fault. She tried to fix the issue, and offered me a new lasagna whole the clock shows 9:00 pm. I said please don't, but she insisted. Well, there is the picture of the same plate that she brought. I guess the chef put more cheese on top, and place into the brick oven until burn it.
I never will back to that place where the only 2 good thing was de waitress service and the salad for US$88.00 (inc. Tip).
Sadly, here is not option less than 1 star because they broke a record for bad quality food.", 'time': 1662003864, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Olivia Leary', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117092694732777585912/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu_ILf5xEc3nXouBTcxYR15uVG5qa-6RZ-RF90mIFA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '4 months ago', 'text': 'We have ordered from Bertucci‚Äôs a dozen times and always enjoyed the food. Tonight was a different story- and so bad that we will likely never return. TLDR: it took 3 hours to get our order and the pizza was inedible. See photo. Order at your own risk.

We ordered through Grubhub and our order was delayed multiple times. My husband called to check in and they said it would not take as long as Grubhub was estimating and that they were just behind because of their BOGO pizza deal on Tuesdays. BOGO pizza deal? Uhhh well we paid full price through Grubhub. The manager was shocked to learn the discount doesn‚Äôt show up for Grubhub customers. First issue. My husband very politely explained how long we‚Äôve been waiting and we were offered a future free pizza. Fine.

More delays later our order is randomly cancelled via Grubhub. My husband calls again. They are shocked to learn the order was cancelled‚Ä¶ not sure how that works but ok‚Ä¶ so they tell him the pizzas just came out of the oven and they will give them to us for free if I want to come get it. Fine. Off I go to pick it up.

I show up at the restaurant, which was empty by the way, except for a few people waiting for takeout. Come to find out our order is NOT ready. There was no presence from the manager. He came around to put some things into the POS system and never acknowledged any of the weary customers who had been waiting for hours. Never apologized, and never even appeared to have any sense of urgency to get the restaurant back on track.

Finally the pizza was done and it was absolutely disgusting. The dough was practically uncooked yet the cheese was burned. We threw it away. After over 3 hours of waiting, we were left hungry.

If a pizza restaurant can‚Äôt manage to make pizzas- the literal bare minimum- what else isn‚Äôt being managed there? Are the employees washing their hands? Makes you wonder. We‚Äôre so turned off by the ridiculous wait, poor food quality and lack of management intervention that we will likely not return. It‚Äôs very disappointing because we previously loved it. But this experience was beyond ridiculous.', 'time': 1654653076, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Karen Garcia, Realtor - Woodbridge, VA', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114241674952387155338/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu_R4xncqnHRunMhBiYqv7InNi-unjWXeLVHaeKRwg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '5 months ago', 'text': 'Haven‚Äôt been to Bertucci‚Äôs in years. The sirloin tips are so tender and have a delicious char. The cod and French fries were very fresh (definitely not from frozen)!

Overall, great prices for much better than expected food! Their service has always been great - the waitstaff has always been so friendly and hospitable.

Their breakfast buffet is delicious and hard to beat for $14.99!', 'time': 1662249289, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'James Koontz', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106187796780883076911/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-ObI_l9OBspKfy-rMx4DFgXtliXmgz073aSd0fYxA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': "Good chili, good craft beer choices, and good prices. And, if you can eat outside, it can be a great experience.

Unfortunately, if you want to eat inside, just know that you will come out smelling like smoke. reviews: [{'author_name': 'Javier Chavez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102402309949326815837/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9OipFmctyKQMlM7zXxIVhA0D9TdsQnLyfwKjLtMw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': "What a coincidence! Reina was our server and she was very nice and attentive.', 'time': 1655836755, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Stephen Bozeman', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103993391525800528532/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu-qh067KgtTrLE_umJQiwAOLQ6Kry0njXQCn9h2iA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '8 months ago', 'text': "This is our first time here and we absolutely loved it! I feel like we're still allowed to have ethnicity and food comparisons and in fact family run ethnic business are extremely proud of the ethnic food they prepare and serve. name: Bob Evans
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Melissa Gagliardo', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111667819714846977852/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9xMdn42CyFw81UupKIAMZKCv3ZYc1Orr76incVjw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'We ordered from Bob Evans via UberEats, so I wasn't expecting the food to be fresh or hot, but our experience was just pitiful.

My husband order a bowl of chicken noodle soup and a side of fries. The "bowl" of soup was a small cup that was about 2/3rds filled. The "broth" was at least 75% grease, and completely inedible. The side of fries was tiny and they had a strange bitter aftertaste, definitely not worth $3.50.

I ordered a half sandwich and a side salad. The sandwich was a little soggy, but otherwise okay. The salad would have been fine, but I received tartar sauce in place of the ranch dressing.

My son's mac and cheese was pretty good.

Maybe they're good in person, but I would not recommend ordering from here.', 'time': 1659830310, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Javier Chavez', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102402309949326815837/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu9OipFmctyKQMlM7zXxIVhA0D9TdsQnLyfwKjLtMw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': "I've driven by Bob Evans so many times, finally got a chance to go in. Did not disappoint. We went there mid afternoon,  so it was empty.  We had an early dinner, it was great and filling,  comfort food as they call it. Had the chicken fried steak, very filling. I need to go there for breakfast,  seems like it would be great.", 'time': 1657653570, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Figueroa Esq', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106198422882997500586/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu8dnI87nho8fivF2Sr8VAiC-ktMmfebYNItr8I=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'It was a DISASTER!

From the beginning to the end, not worth returning.

We arrived and no one, but I mean no one even acknowledged we were there.

After around 8 min mark someone said have you been talking care of? I was second in line and obviously the first clients were there before us.

People were leaving angry, at one point one of the servers said to a female who got up and left, "I hope you get better service next time."  At least the server was honest. Thumbs üëçup for that.

But let's analyze what the server said, "I hope..." at no moment did the server say, come back, you WILL get better service next time.

To be fair, we got there a bit after, what I assume was the morning rush time.

FOOD

Not worth the price, due to no flavor and poor quality control, EXTREMELY OVERPRICED.

By now you know me. If food is on point, a high price is a fair price.

I got the NEW, Farmers Berry Choice with hashbrowns  and French Toast.

The ham was the only good item. Eggs had no flavor. Hashbrowns dull. Again zero flavor. Cardboard is tastier.

The French, would be insulted if they knew, that Bob Evans in Springfield Va, was serving a French Toast with a wierd aftertaste. It had no flavors, just sweetness, and again, the aftertaste was horrible. Like if it was cooked using old ingredients...

Yeah, definitely not a pleasant experience.  I was surprised. I hadn't gone in a while, before covid, and food and service was much better.

I had to leave the French Toast. Couldn't take it  And I have eaten some wierd stuff but this one is in a category of its own.

The bisquets were a bit too salty, go figure.

Coffee was decent. Can you imagine, the free coffee was ok. But the food would be sent back from the devil himself.

SERVER:

Seemed a bit rushed but was professional. I was able to get a smile from her. So that coupled with the ham and coffee is the reason of two stars.

BATHROOMS:

Men's was clean.

RETURN FACTOR:
30%  I may return at a less busy time to see if they can get it right.

RECOMMEND A FRIEND FACTOR:

ZERO!

If I recommend a friend I assure you that will be the last day I can call that person a friend.

RECOMMENDATIONS:

Management must get the quality control back in check.

Management, go over the menu with the cooks. See how they are cooking it. What ingredients are used? Are the cooking oils fresh? Have them taste the fruit of their labor to see if they can identify what is needed to make it better.

And if they still do it wrong, let the cook find another place to screw up, not Bob Evans.

Thank God I didn't order the family meal I wanted.', 'time': 1630794561, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'coachie 4life', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107811770800191005597/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu96mgvJ9J_D_jnG6ZdHgh-USq2I_xBGFPrH26shfg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'My family and I have frequent Bob Evans many times... way before the Pandemic.  Most of the Staff we knew are no longer working there. Recently, we visited and noticed that there was only one waitress on duty name Crissy and there were quite a bit of customers in the restaurant.  She appeared to be overwhelmed but pushed through it and did a magnificent job. Although my Sunshine Skillet was horrible, the Cook really tried to keep up and did a better job with the Pancakes. I felt the female Manager on duty could have assisted her more. I recommend that they hire more staff.  I really felt sorry for her. Keep up the good work Crissy.', 'time': 1659334531, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Sara Marlatt', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117022757661111784647/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu0XHSuKcquizCa0usuCgq16c13SPamsiQYJ7Fz3Sw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "Typically Bob Evan's restaurants are consistent with food quality and service. With little kids, we often stop at a local store while traveling since it's reliable, family and budget friendly. This location changed my opinion on the overall consistency and reliability though. If you're traveling and looking for a quick bite or have kids and want something to please everyone, do not stop at this Bob Evan's.

Omelette was hard and overcooked. Homefries tasted like leftovers that had been deep fried. Burger bun was greasy, but the burger was tough and chewy. Wildfire chicken salad didn't have any wildfire bqq, cheese, or onions, and the chicken was tough and crunchy, again like leftovers that were deep fried a second or third time. Sausage gravy had a film on top, as if it had been sitting under a heat lamp for a long time, but it was barely warm.

Our server was friendly, but had zero menu knowledge. She told us just point to what you want on the menu cause I don't know what most of it is. My husband ordered the 3 meat omelette and she asked what do you want in your omelette, I don't know what that is? We ordered turkey, mashed potatoes, and corn for our 2 yr old, and the server asked the sandwich? She came back twice to ask about our bread choices. Then came back 2 more times because she forgot what sides we ordered.

The food did take a little longer than usual, especially since there were only 2 or 3 other tables with guests.

Overall, as a parent and Bob Evan's lover, I was not impressed! My husband and I didn't even finish our meals. My kids were happy with their pancakes, turkey lurkey dinner, and fries (2 bites of the burger and my daughter said nope) though.", 'time': 1626055022, 'translated': False}]

After reading the gleaming reviews I thought to myself, this must be the best place for sushi.....

Couldn't wait to go, but once there.... Well, my humble opinion, much better places everywhere.

FOOD:

We ordered 4 different sushi plates
Beef bento box and fried ice cream.

Sushi, maybe for someone who has never compared to other sushi places, it may be good.

But it wasn't close. The sushi didn't taste as fresh as other locations. Something wierd about the taste. The fish did not have the consistency or texture I have tasted previously.

Disclaimer, I don't like seafood but for you guys I will taste every food out there.

Beef Bento, beef was over cooked, which made it hard and chewy. The sauce was not salty.

The dumplings were extremely oily! It was like putting a spoon full of oil in your mouth. First time I've had fried dumplings so oily. See pictures.

The other fried items, onions, sweat potatoes,etc.. were spot on.  üëå

The best item was the fried ice cream. Together, the fried coating and vanilla ice cream made sense. All textures matched perfectly. My two cents, maybe ask the client if they may wish some warm chocolate to give the flavors an added dimension. The constant flavors can get boring.  But this dish is definitely the only reason I would return. Go figure.

LOCATION

It's next to a major strip mall, in a small section with plenty of parking.

RESTAURANT

Small, tight. Not a place for a romantic or business meeting.

CUSTOMER SERVICE

Lovely.  Tom was excellent, knowledgeable and caring.  Only because of Tom, the restaurant should be 5 üåü.

BATHROOMS

Clean and decent.

RETURN FACTOR

10% To buy Fried Ice Cream

RECOMMEND A FRIEND FACTOR

0%

SUMMARY

They have strong potential but they need to get that quality control in check.

I will return to see if this was just a wrong turn along the way.', 'time': 1637434867, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Jen Massabki', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114847010428392351461/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu3LCC60Z-y-3wxSbe1HD1QdV1jMFo0NvHxEUHqa=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Excellent sushi!!!! This order was a customer pickup done on the Maggiano's website.  I don't even have a Door Dash account.

Even if it was a third party, how on earth would the quality of my meal have anything to do with a delivery service?  I've amended my review from two stars to one.

Original review: This was our first order from Maggiano's since before the pandemic.  It was our wedding anniversary and we decided to stay in, splurge a bit and order out from one of our favorite places.

Firstly, after my husband arrived and checked in, he was acknowledged and then ignored for ages.  I called the restaurant to remind them he was outside, and they responded in such a manner that I can only assume he'd been forgotten.

Okay, no big whoop.  Maybe they were super busy.

Then I opened the food.  The fettucine portion was not very large for two people. It was dry and hard and the sauce had seeped down to the bottom of the container in a sad sticky puddle.  I sighed, but tried to make the best of it.  I stirred as best I could, cut the lump in half with a spatula and flipped it upside down so my husband wouldn't see how bad it looked.

Then I opened the salad.  What.the.fudge.  The avocado I paid extra for was so old it had turned black.  Not just brown from being cut and sitting for awhile, black and rotten. (see photos) One of the three cherry tomatoes had a black rotten spot.  The croutons no longer had an iota of crunch - they kind of sadly dissolved when eaten.

One of the loaves of bread was burned.  (I think some people like it that way, but it should be an option, not a default.) Had to throw it out it was so hard inside and out.

The cheesecake - pretty darn good.  Large portion, fresh strawberries, sauce and whipped cream.   And my husband liked his chicken parmesan.   Two stars.

Overall, it was $80 worth of mostly garbage.  So much food thrown away!  I didn't feel well at all for two days - likely from the salad I tried to salvage since my husband was fine.  I should've just tossed all of it.

Come on, Maggiano's.  Shameful!", 'time': 1661455284, 'translated': False}, {'author_name': 'Eric Parker', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101615194084128764901/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'original_language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACNPEu97W2UIU49V0Cpi_NZoWcEjsxLyOUypzy7YgRAbng=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Had a great time here, it actually was my first time going. In the frozen section I like the Magnolia brand of mango ice cream (OMG!), I‚Äôd pick up some breakfast/lunch meat like chicken longanisa (sausage), chicken or pork tocino (marinated meat on the sweet side) , tapa (marinated beef on the salty side), chicken siopao (stuffed steamed buns I love the brand Oriental chicken or Magnolia ... microwave covered with wet paper towel), smoked fish bangus (the head is still on on this one. I cook it in the oven).  These are the ones I‚Äôve tried and usually get.

My Lola made all kinds of salads growing up with fresh mangos, papayas, basil, lettuce, and other veggies. She would grill eggplant etc. I wish they had some and her tinola/sinigang are sometimes vegan when eaten as a side dish. My kids are not big on rice. Laing is good but other choices will be nice. Maybe when this store gets bigger.

I will be back and I will post an update.', 'time': 1596461116, 'translated': False}]
